  "title": "Auditory single word recognition in MEG",
  "description": "This dataset comprises magnetoencephalography (MEG) recordings of auditory single word recognition in human subjects. Participants listened to isolated words from the Massive Auditory Lexical Decision (MALD) database while neural activity was recorded, providing insights into the temporal dynamics of auditory word comprehension. The dataset includes raw MEG data, stimulus information, and associated metadata, formatted according to the Brain Imaging Data Structure (BIDS) standard.",
